They've done well to get here.
They've surprised a few people by getting this far. They haven't looked that impressive, to be honest. I'm confident my boys will have too much for them today.

I respect what they've done.
You'd have to say nobody expected them to get this far in the competition. You have to respect what they've already achieved. So my boys won't be under-estimating them.
The opposition aren't my responsibility.

Will being at home give you the edge?

We'll do our job anywhere.
Of course you can say that being at home can give a team an advantage. But it's not a big deal for us. We go out with the same attitude wherever we play.
We're strong at home.
I'd have to say that home advantage can help us. It lifts the whole team, playing in front of our own fans. I think can only be a positive for the boys.
We try to be professional in our approach.
At %1s, we try to be professional in our approach to every game. We always prepare properly. I don't think whether we're at home or away has any impact on our performances.
So much to play for! Can your boys do it?
It's a massive game anyway and the stakes are even higher because you're up against fierce rivals. How are you feeling? Can you get the better of %1s?
We're ready to take the game to them.
I sense a great determination in our dressing room. We've come this far in the competition and we don't want to miss out now. We'll go out and try to dominate the game from the very start.
I hope we'll be mentally ready.
I've not been impressed with some of what I've witnessed in training this week. The last thing I want to see is a sense of complacency. If we're going to win, we're going to need to be at our best.
It's not going to be easy.
A high-pressure game against a %1s team that's in good form, and we're dealing with fatigue after a busy run of matches. For sure, today won't be easy at all.
What frame of mind will your players be in?

We want to be in the best frame of mind.
The culture here at %1s is to send teams out with an aggressive and professional attitude for every game. We'll make sure that's the frame of mind the lads will be in today.
The lads are winners!
We pride ourselves on our winning mentality. We're not concerned that people judge %1s to be the stronger team. We'll still go into the game believing we can come out on top.
Attitude's important, that's for sure.
I know how important my players' attitude is going into every game. Mental strength gives you physical strength. We'll need both today.
How do you handle the pressure?

We'll be ready to deal with the situation.
These players are mentally strong. They've been in games when the odds are against them before. That can actually take pressure off us. We'll just go out and play as well as we can.
Everybody feels pressure.
We all feel the pressure: the players, the coaching staff. Even the fans! But our opponents will feel it, too. If we're mentally strong, that can give us a chance.
